    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Passing On a Clean Drive</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ernest Kessler letter, responding to Oct 8 article, says it was very informative to learn about kinds of information stored on computer's hard drive</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I found the article ''What's on Your Hard Drive?'' (Oct. 8) of great interest and very timely for me. I will soon be buying a new computer and plan to give my Compaq to a young grandchild. So, of course, I want to be sure that nothing of a personal nature remains on the hard drive.</p>
        <p>ERNEST KESSLER  Hackensack, N.J., Oct. 9, 1998</p>
      </block>
